  "body": "When a user has a directory structure in the root of the project such as:\r\n\r\n```\r\n├── contracts\r\n│   ├── $###.sol\r\n├── contracts_ext\r\n│   ├── $###.sol\r\n```\r\n\r\nhardhat will try and compile contracts in both directories even when explicitly setting \r\n\r\n```typescript\r\nconst config: HardhatUserConfig = {\r\n  paths: {\r\n    sources: './contracts',\r\n    tests: './test',\r\n    cache: './cache',\r\n    artifacts: './artifacts',\r\n  },\r\n{ ... }\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\nchanging the directory name fixes the issue, e.g:\r\n\r\n```\r\n├── contracts\r\n│   ├── $###.sol\r\n├── ext_contracts\r\n│   ├── $###.sol\r\n```",
